1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
A state transition needs a domain-specific state space.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Polyhedral manipulation uses face contact as state.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Machine assembly uses part mating as state.

4
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Knot tying uses topology as state.

5
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Dance uses key pose and foot contact as state.

6
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Different representations ignore different irrelevant variations.

7
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:18,000
The shared principle is task-relevant state change.
